WEBVTT

00:10.468 --> 00:12.887
THE FOLLOWING CONTAINS
DEPICTIONS OF SELF-HARM,

00:12.971 --> 00:15.056
WHICH MAY BE DISTURBING FOR SOME VIEWERS.

00:42.083 --> 00:44.586
MARCH 12, 2005
DO HYE-RYUNG

01:03.188 --> 01:05.440
You're wondering what the bitch is up to?

01:11.863 --> 01:13.364
The rules are simple.

01:15.533 --> 01:18.411
You write down your saju and make a wish,

01:20.205 --> 01:21.623
and it comes true.

01:29.547 --> 01:31.132
You have no idea.

01:35.053 --> 01:37.514
I'll make the wish
just the way you wanted.

01:38.515 --> 01:40.016
My wish is…

01:44.479 --> 01:46.314
for all of you to die.

01:46.981 --> 01:50.026
I truly want every single one of you dead.

02:08.670 --> 02:10.296
That's my true wish.

02:23.518 --> 02:30.525
MARCH 12, 2005
DO HYE-RYUNG

02:31.943 --> 02:38.283
IF WISHES COULD KILL

02:39.367 --> 02:41.077
THURSDAY, JUNE 12

03:19.490 --> 03:20.325
AUNT JI-SUN

03:20.408 --> 03:22.660
EMERGENCY AT THE HOSPITAL
LEAVING MY CARD FOR YOU

03:28.625 --> 03:31.920
YOU SLEEPING?

03:34.923 --> 03:35.757
READ JUST NOW

03:41.596 --> 03:42.597
I'M UPPP

03:42.680 --> 03:44.682
I GUESS YOU'RE STILL SLEEPING…

03:46.434 --> 03:48.728
I'LL HEAD OUT WITHOUT YOU TODAY…

03:48.811 --> 03:50.355
NO! I'M HEADING OUT NOW!

04:02.659 --> 04:04.244
Hey.

04:04.327 --> 04:07.038
You're not supposed to run in the halls.
You'll wake the neighbors.

04:07.664 --> 04:11.626
I'm sorry. I should really
get up earlier one of these days.

04:11.709 --> 04:12.543
Hm.

04:22.303 --> 04:23.554
Did you

04:24.389 --> 04:25.890
just… hm?

04:26.432 --> 04:27.850
What? I'm sorry.

04:27.934 --> 04:28.977
I won't do it again.

04:29.060 --> 04:30.311
No! I liked it very much.

04:30.395 --> 04:33.189
I liked it so much
I'd love it if you did it again. One more?

04:33.815 --> 04:34.857
One more time.

04:34.941 --> 04:37.443
One more time. One more…

04:41.614 --> 04:42.907
Good morning, Mr. Kim.

04:47.245 --> 04:48.371
TODAY'S FORTUNE

04:49.580 --> 04:50.999
And love?

04:51.082 --> 04:53.751
"Speak your true feelings."

05:00.425 --> 05:01.342
Oh!

05:03.886 --> 05:05.179
You can drop me off here.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.182
What? No. No, wait. It's too dangerous!

05:16.274 --> 05:17.108
Oh.

05:26.034 --> 05:26.909
Na-ri?

05:27.994 --> 05:29.746
Na-ri.

05:33.082 --> 05:34.083
You ready?

05:37.128 --> 05:39.839
Geon-woo, what are you doing after school?

05:39.922 --> 05:42.258
-Yo, secret attack!
-Jesus, you scared me!

05:42.342 --> 05:44.802
-You shit.
-My bad. Sorry.

05:45.845 --> 05:47.180
Ugh. Idiot.

05:53.061 --> 05:54.354
What's wrong?

05:54.437 --> 05:57.607
I'm only saying this because I've known
both of you since middle school.

05:58.649 --> 05:59.942
Why are you always together now?

06:03.571 --> 06:04.697
You dating?

06:05.740 --> 06:08.409
Yeah, sure. You're being crazy.

06:08.493 --> 06:09.786
Yeah.

06:09.869 --> 06:12.038
We both live
in the same apartment building, loser.

06:12.121 --> 06:13.915
Why would we get to school separately?

06:14.415 --> 06:18.044
No, no, no.
Se-ah usually gets to class early.

06:18.127 --> 06:20.213
You always slide in at the last minute.

06:20.797 --> 06:21.756
But these days,

06:21.839 --> 06:24.550
you guys are both on time together.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.804
I smell a rat. It's fishy.

06:28.471 --> 06:29.305
Right, Na-ri?

06:29.889 --> 06:31.307
Yeah.

06:31.933 --> 06:34.560
I say this because I've known you
since elementary school.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.647
What did you eat
to make your breath so gross?

06:39.607 --> 06:40.733
Checkmate.

06:41.234 --> 06:42.860
Why this extreme reaction?

06:45.238 --> 06:46.823
So, yeah, my guess is

06:47.990 --> 06:50.159
you also have a crush
on Geon-woo, don't ya?

06:50.243 --> 06:52.120
-Yeah.
-No.

06:53.121 --> 06:54.247
Oh!

06:54.330 --> 06:55.790
I'm in love with Geon-woo.

06:57.583 --> 06:59.335
Why don't we just put it out in the open?

06:59.877 --> 07:02.422
Oh! Now I turn the game on you.

07:02.505 --> 07:03.464
Wanna play?

07:03.965 --> 07:04.882
Let's go.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.676
I love you, too, Na-ri.

07:08.886 --> 07:11.722
Say that again
and I'll make sure you fucking die.

07:13.307 --> 07:15.852
Fuck. What a shitty
start to the day. Seriously.

07:15.935 --> 07:16.936
Poor baby.

07:17.019 --> 07:20.565
Stop talking. Stop making
things awkward all the time, you otaku.

07:20.648 --> 07:23.401
You're a menace. I'll take care of him.

07:24.610 --> 07:26.571
Honestly, not so rough!

07:26.654 --> 07:28.406
My neck is my best attribute.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.453
SEORIN MIDDLE &amp; HIGH SCHOOL

07:35.872 --> 07:39.208
If you end up using the A ones,
just make sure they're labeled correctly.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.324
Yo, Ha-joon.

08:12.408 --> 08:13.910
I almost got killed by Geon-woo today.

08:16.162 --> 08:17.872
-In a headlock?
-Whoa!

08:17.955 --> 08:20.708
You are the smartest kid
in the class. Hold on.

08:23.961 --> 08:25.588
This won't turn on. Keeps crashing.

08:25.671 --> 08:28.007
I'm really busy right now.

08:28.090 --> 08:30.051
How about you fix it
as a present for my birthday?

08:30.134 --> 08:31.427
I told you. I can't.

08:31.511 --> 08:33.763
My old PIN is the new one. Thank you.

08:36.641 --> 08:38.726
-You wanna hear something cray-cray?
-No.

08:39.435 --> 08:40.561
Se-ah and…

08:43.147 --> 08:44.232
What about Se-ah?

08:46.067 --> 08:47.860
Se-ah and Geon-woo are--

08:47.944 --> 08:49.320
Hello, all. Good morning!

08:49.904 --> 08:51.822
-Good morning, Teacher.
-We'll talk later.

08:51.906 --> 08:55.910
My beloved students,
Class 2-4 are ready for the future.

08:58.371 --> 09:02.250
In your last mock exam, our class took
first place in math in the whole city.

09:02.333 --> 09:03.709
Oh!

09:03.793 --> 09:06.629
There were only four students
who got perfect scores,

09:06.712 --> 09:07.964
and two of them are here.

09:08.047 --> 09:08.965
What?

09:09.048 --> 09:11.217
I'm sure you all know one of them.

09:13.302 --> 09:15.137
Ha-joon. Way to go!

09:20.434 --> 09:22.603
And the other perfect scorer is…

09:22.687 --> 09:23.604
Hm.

09:24.105 --> 09:25.565
-Hyeong-wook.
-What?

09:26.649 --> 09:27.817
Give him a hand.

09:30.778 --> 09:31.988
Hyeong-wook?

09:34.240 --> 09:36.576
I know. I was surprised too.

09:36.659 --> 09:40.288
It's hard to believe,
but he also needs your applause.

09:44.417 --> 09:46.961
Amazing job, you two!

09:47.545 --> 09:50.089
-He cheated.
-This is a joke.

09:50.172 --> 09:52.216
-Should be an investigation.
-Investigation?

09:52.300 --> 09:53.676
Yes!

09:53.759 --> 09:56.137
Do that on your own time.

09:58.931 --> 10:00.391
Oh, yes, I almost forgot.

10:00.474 --> 10:02.602
Any of you applying
for the youth club activity?

10:02.685 --> 10:04.186
The forms are here.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.981
No? Anyone going to university?

10:16.699 --> 10:19.327
GIRIGO:
YOUR WISH HAS BEEN GRANTED.

10:19.410 --> 10:22.455
Hyeong-wook, just tell us
if you cheated on the test.

10:22.538 --> 10:24.290
We'll forgive you. Okay?

10:24.373 --> 10:26.709
Tell us, Ha-joon.
Did you feed him the answers?

10:26.792 --> 10:28.628
There's no way. We even switched seats.

10:28.711 --> 10:30.963
What are you gonna do
when the police show up to school?

10:31.047 --> 10:33.633
The police will never know the truth.

10:34.258 --> 10:36.969
All this is so boring.
What are we doing here?

10:37.053 --> 10:38.846
Just tell us.

10:40.848 --> 10:42.933
You guys want to know the real truth?

10:47.021 --> 10:48.606
I know something you all don't.

10:54.070 --> 10:55.154
It's Girigo.

10:55.821 --> 10:57.948
What? Girigo?

10:58.032 --> 11:01.494
That's right. It's an app
that grants you wishes.

11:02.286 --> 11:04.372
I'm already tired of listening to this.

11:04.455 --> 11:08.501
Let's stay in the real world, okay? I've
tried to understand you, like a friend.

11:08.584 --> 11:12.088
And I'm totally on board with that.
But this is a little too much.

11:12.171 --> 11:13.547
This is going way too far.

11:13.631 --> 11:15.299
No. This isn't fake. It's real.

11:15.383 --> 11:18.052
There really is an app, uh,
that can grant you wishes.

11:18.135 --> 11:21.555
-I can't find it.
-I mean, why would you even look it up?

11:21.639 --> 11:26.185
Wow. You just made a whole situation
all about you. Again.

11:26.268 --> 11:29.522
You can't search it.
You'll never find it with your phone.

11:30.523 --> 11:33.693
Okay, watch this.
I'll send you the link. One time only.

11:33.776 --> 11:34.860
There you go.

11:42.243 --> 11:44.161
GIRIGO:
DO YOU WANT TO INSTALL THIS APP?

11:44.245 --> 11:45.371
Geon-woo?

11:45.454 --> 11:46.872
You're totally gonna get hacked.

11:46.956 --> 11:50.167
You're the only one who cares. Aren't you
all curious how he got a perfect score?

11:50.251 --> 11:53.587
Personally, I think this app
should be tested thoroughly.

11:54.213 --> 11:55.089
Don't you?

11:56.507 --> 11:58.092
GIRIGO

12:04.265 --> 12:05.266
Hello?

12:06.016 --> 12:08.686
Why does it turn on the camera?
That's weird.

12:09.353 --> 12:10.521
Let me see that.

12:11.272 --> 12:12.356
This is the record button.

12:12.440 --> 12:13.899
So, what is it recording?

12:13.983 --> 12:15.401
All your wishes.

12:15.901 --> 12:19.613
Oh, wait. You have to write
your name and your saju on paper first.

12:19.697 --> 12:20.906
Saju?

12:21.574 --> 12:23.701
You mean like the Four Pillars of Destiny?

12:23.784 --> 12:27.329
Sort of. You write your birth date
and your name on a piece of paper,

12:27.413 --> 12:28.998
hold it up to the screen.

12:29.081 --> 12:31.500
hit the button to record,
and you say your wish.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.919
But you have to really mean it.
Like, for real.

12:35.546 --> 12:38.799
When you're done recording your wish,
make sure to hit the send button here.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.843
-That's it.
-Really? That's it?

12:43.888 --> 12:46.265
I can't believe you even managed
to find something like that.

12:46.974 --> 12:48.350
Let's just say I have my ways.

12:48.434 --> 12:49.977
This app made your wish come true?

12:50.060 --> 12:52.480
Compassion begins where judgment ends.

12:54.231 --> 12:56.525
-I guess you want proof?
-Yeah, show us the proof, man.

12:59.820 --> 13:01.530
Exhibit A.

13:03.157 --> 13:04.784
This is my wish video. Watch.

13:06.535 --> 13:07.828
My wish is…

13:07.912 --> 13:09.205
JUNE 14, 2008
CHOI HYEONG-WOOK

13:09.288 --> 13:10.790
…to get a perfect score in math.

13:11.749 --> 13:13.417
Please let me ace the test for a change.

13:13.501 --> 13:15.252
Perfect score.

13:15.336 --> 13:17.296
What is that?

13:17.379 --> 13:20.257
-Perfect score.
-That's so stupid!

13:21.509 --> 13:22.343
Wow.

13:22.426 --> 13:25.888
It makes me question why the hell
I've stayed your friend for so long.

13:29.225 --> 13:33.395
Hey. Where are you guys going? I have more
proof. You haven't seen all of it yet.

13:36.190 --> 13:37.024
Listen to me.

13:37.107 --> 13:39.860
I understand that you're under
a lot of stress because of your grades.

13:39.944 --> 13:41.237
I get that.

13:41.320 --> 13:44.448
But just cut it out.
Stop being weird all the time. Hm?

13:45.533 --> 13:46.534
Exhibit A, point two.

13:46.617 --> 13:48.744
The message I got
when my wish was granted…

13:50.246 --> 13:51.080
Whoa.

13:51.163 --> 13:52.206
What's this?

14:01.257 --> 14:02.091
Oh!

14:03.133 --> 14:04.134
It's a countdown.

14:07.930 --> 14:09.807
-Hey, move!
-Slow down!

14:16.438 --> 14:18.315
Just a little more.

14:21.819 --> 14:23.529
Oh, starving yourself again?

14:23.612 --> 14:25.364
I've gained back everything I've lost.

14:25.447 --> 14:27.700
Sounds extreme
just for Hyeong-wook's birthday party.

14:27.783 --> 14:31.161
Are you dumb? He's not a baby. Why would
he even have a stupid party anyway?

14:31.245 --> 14:32.788
Come on. He's kindhearted.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.498
Ugh. Kindhearted.

14:34.582 --> 14:37.459
You know, calling him kindhearted
only worked back in middle school.

14:37.543 --> 14:39.461
He's embarrassing, smelly, and boring.

14:39.545 --> 14:42.006
Okay. What did he do to deserve that?

14:43.090 --> 14:46.719
Were you not there when we watched
his stupid video earlier? We all saw.

14:46.802 --> 14:50.306
It was ridiculous already
to make a wish on some weird app.

14:50.389 --> 14:51.599
A perfect score in math?

14:51.682 --> 14:53.142
Jesus.

14:53.225 --> 14:54.935
What a pathetic wish for a pathetic nerd.

14:55.019 --> 14:57.229
He even picked a wish
that suits him perfectly.

15:00.190 --> 15:03.485
His family's been really sensitive
about his grades.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.321
Maybe he was trying
to make them proud of him.

15:05.404 --> 15:09.283
Boo-hoo! You think that loser
ever thinks about anyone but himself?

15:15.080 --> 15:18.083
By the way, I wonder
what Geon-woo will wear this weekend.

15:19.209 --> 15:20.628
Can you ask him for me?

15:23.213 --> 15:24.423
Why should I?

15:25.174 --> 15:27.176
Oh, that's right. You shouldn't.

15:32.181 --> 15:34.767
Did you get Hyeong-wook
a birthday present?

15:35.434 --> 15:39.188
Ugh, no. I don't know.
It stresses me out.

15:39.271 --> 15:40.731
I really don't get why Geon-woo

15:40.814 --> 15:43.817
puts up with Hyeong-wook's otaku geek crap
all the time.

15:43.901 --> 15:46.737
He pulls that shit on me now
because Geon-woo is there.

15:47.655 --> 15:50.658
If I were you, I'd stop putting up
with Hyeong-wook's silly behavior too.

15:50.741 --> 15:53.285
-He'll only bring you down.
-That's harsh, Na-ri.

15:53.369 --> 15:55.913
Just his face makes me so pissed off.

15:55.996 --> 15:57.164
When is enough, enough?

15:57.247 --> 15:59.375
We've all grown up,
but he stays dull and immature.

15:59.458 --> 16:01.377
-Wouldn't be shocked if he wore diapers--
-Enough!

16:10.010 --> 16:11.595
Why'd you guys stop all of a sudden?

16:12.221 --> 16:13.806
Are you talking about girl stuff?

16:16.558 --> 16:18.560
Uh, it's, uh…

16:18.644 --> 16:20.646
Were you spying on my conversation?

16:23.065 --> 16:24.358
Actually, we're…

16:27.820 --> 16:30.155
talking about your present, you big goof.

16:32.116 --> 16:35.035
It's supposed to be a surprise.
It'd be ruined if you found out now.

16:35.119 --> 16:38.831
I knew my ears were burning.
When you arrived, you got really quiet.

16:39.832 --> 16:41.917
No presents necessary. Just yourselves.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.669
Asking for a gift is so out of fashion.

16:43.752 --> 16:47.715
Nuh-uh, a little present with a big bow,
all wrapped up in your favorite colors.

16:48.340 --> 16:49.258
Yes, my lady.

16:49.341 --> 16:50.718
As you wish.

16:52.136 --> 16:54.513
You're gonna be late
for training. Let's go.

16:54.596 --> 16:57.349
Oh, you mustn't be late. Without delay.

16:57.433 --> 16:58.684
Make haste.

17:00.310 --> 17:03.188
Honestly, don't worry about the gifts.
Having you there is present enough.

17:14.575 --> 17:17.578
Now, for any two real numbers,

17:18.203 --> 17:23.417
x1 and x2 in some interval
of the function f(x),

17:24.668 --> 17:27.171
if x1 is less than x2

17:28.005 --> 17:32.551
and f(x1) is greater than
or equal to f(x2),

17:32.634 --> 17:34.845
then f is a decreasing function.

17:35.345 --> 17:39.016
So, what would the opposite be
in an increasing function?

17:39.725 --> 17:42.269
Come on, guys, this one's easy. We just…

18:45.999 --> 18:47.417
We're going to have a guest.

18:47.501 --> 18:49.837
Huh? We're having a guest?

18:49.920 --> 18:51.380
A good one?

18:51.463 --> 18:52.965
Or a bad one?

18:54.133 --> 18:55.259
Haetsal?

19:01.014 --> 19:01.849
What's wrong?

19:04.810 --> 19:06.353
You're scaring me now.

19:08.772 --> 19:11.567
-Should I get my knife?
-I don't know.

19:12.818 --> 19:15.154
I can't see
what kind of guest we're dealing with.

19:18.824 --> 19:20.784
Keep your head up!

19:27.332 --> 19:28.834
Keep it up! Keep it up!

19:35.632 --> 19:36.758
Up and out!

19:38.510 --> 19:41.013
Geon-woo. Get ready.

19:41.513 --> 19:43.015
Come on!

19:51.565 --> 19:52.900
Hit the board.

19:53.942 --> 19:55.027
Focus up.

20:02.492 --> 20:03.368
Whoa! Oh!

20:06.121 --> 20:10.000
He practically flies off the mat,
but always bails at the sandpit.

20:10.500 --> 20:11.376
Three.

20:11.919 --> 20:13.670
Hey, Geon-woo. Come here.

20:15.464 --> 20:18.300
Wasn't it the same foul
that got you disqualified last year?

20:18.383 --> 20:20.510
-I think so, yeah.
-You know exactly.

20:20.594 --> 20:24.848
You haven't even made one single proper
jump in competition this year either.

20:24.932 --> 20:27.601
You have to get out of your head
and control your nerves.

20:27.684 --> 20:29.728
Focus, and get in the game, okay?

20:29.811 --> 20:31.813
Try it again.
Get back on the starting line.

20:41.531 --> 20:43.533
Just do it like you're practicing.

20:44.618 --> 20:46.870
Yeah, that's easy for you to say.

20:46.954 --> 20:48.455
-One.
-Okay.

20:50.249 --> 20:53.835
Before you run, say this little mantra,
and empty your mind completely.

20:53.919 --> 20:55.879
"The entire world is this moment."

20:55.963 --> 20:57.130
"Only this remains."

20:57.214 --> 20:58.465
Say it, and believe it.

20:58.548 --> 21:01.134
As soon as you're ready,
release like an arrow, and you jump.

21:01.218 --> 21:03.971
Is that what you do every time you jump?

21:05.097 --> 21:06.223
Not exactly.

21:06.723 --> 21:09.309
I just go for it.

21:23.365 --> 21:26.493
ASBESTOS REMOVAL IN PROGRESS
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

22:03.280 --> 22:07.034
Are you on any medication?
Like painkillers or cold pills?

22:07.117 --> 22:09.578
Absolutely not!
What are you accusing me of?

22:09.661 --> 22:11.538
Hormone shots? Birth control?

22:11.621 --> 22:14.583
-Coach, I swear, I would never--
-The national reserve team called.

22:16.752 --> 22:17.586
What?

22:20.839 --> 22:23.633
Why the whole interrogation
before letting me know?!

22:23.717 --> 22:27.054
Here on in, you're on special training.
After school and also weekends.

22:27.137 --> 22:29.389
We need to sharpen your skills
as much as possible.

22:29.473 --> 22:31.058
And please don't embarrass me.

22:31.141 --> 22:32.851
I'll do my very best!

22:32.934 --> 22:34.686
Oh, Coach, thank you!

22:34.770 --> 22:36.730
No. No, don't do that!
Keep your hands to yourself!

22:36.813 --> 22:38.190
I don't like being hugged!

22:38.774 --> 22:42.235
What are you gonna do when your weekends
are full and can't date anymore?

22:43.236 --> 22:45.989
You can bring Geon-woo
to train with you if you want.

22:46.073 --> 22:48.075
Before he loses his mind.

22:53.372 --> 22:54.498
I'm sorry, Coach.

22:54.581 --> 22:56.166
Uh, we thought no one knew.

22:57.501 --> 22:59.628
How could I not know?

23:00.212 --> 23:01.463
It's so obvious.

23:07.260 --> 23:09.179
SE-AH

23:12.891 --> 23:14.309
Hey, Se-ah.

23:16.770 --> 23:17.771
You there?

23:21.108 --> 23:22.150
Are you there?

23:24.528 --> 23:25.695
SE-AH

23:26.363 --> 23:27.197
What's going on?

23:47.926 --> 23:49.261
Oh my God.

23:49.761 --> 23:53.223
Hey, are you guys really going
to that pathetic loser's birthday party?

23:53.306 --> 23:56.059
I don't know. Fuck.
I'm sick of taking care of him at school.

23:56.143 --> 23:58.270
Now I have to take care of him
on the weekend too?

23:58.353 --> 23:59.646
That dumbass is so annoying.

23:59.729 --> 24:02.566
"Your presence is my present"?
What the fuck is that?

24:02.649 --> 24:05.652
I totally freaked out when he saw us.
It was embarrassing.

24:06.945 --> 24:08.655
Like, read the room, dude.

24:08.738 --> 24:11.867
I just wish he would stop
following us around all the time.

24:11.950 --> 24:14.119
-I know, right? I hate him.
-Hey!

24:14.202 --> 24:15.829
-Shh!
-Shut up!

24:17.122 --> 24:18.206
Does he know?

24:19.207 --> 24:20.876
SE-AH

24:29.843 --> 24:31.011
CALLING
SE-AH

24:34.639 --> 24:38.101
HYEONG-WOOK

24:43.356 --> 24:46.067
HYEONG-WOOK

24:51.323 --> 24:53.533
-The person you are trying--
-Oh shit.

25:01.208 --> 25:04.085
Geon-woo, I have some great news.

25:06.546 --> 25:07.547
Uh…

25:12.260 --> 25:13.428
Hey, my good friend.

25:13.512 --> 25:15.722
Guess who made the nationals?

25:16.723 --> 25:18.058
Uh…

25:35.700 --> 25:36.535
Yo, Hyeong-wook!

25:42.249 --> 25:43.500
Did he get in trouble again?

25:51.299 --> 25:54.678
Did you see him
during evening study? It was weird.

25:55.387 --> 25:58.473
Hey, why did you finish so late?
We've been waiting for you.

25:58.557 --> 26:01.184
-I had to go to my locker.
-Chill out. I'm coming!

26:13.655 --> 26:15.699
Everyone's gone now.

26:15.782 --> 26:16.741
That took a while.

26:17.367 --> 26:19.119
I made the national team!

26:19.202 --> 26:20.453
What? The national team?

26:20.537 --> 26:22.831
-Oh! You made it! Yes!
-Shh, shh, shh.

26:24.249 --> 26:25.417
-Oh!
-Quiet.

26:26.001 --> 26:27.919
Mm.

26:30.755 --> 26:32.340
Don't be scared.

26:33.717 --> 26:34.676
No way!

26:34.759 --> 26:35.969
It's the exact opposite.

26:36.052 --> 26:38.930
I'm with you. And I'm so proud
you made the national team.

26:44.436 --> 26:45.812
Wow! Crazy.

26:46.313 --> 26:47.397
National team.

26:49.316 --> 26:52.068
Oh, by the way, Coach knows we're dating.

26:52.569 --> 26:53.445
I don't know how.

26:53.528 --> 26:54.404
What?

26:54.946 --> 26:56.781
-Well, did you tell her?
-No.

26:56.865 --> 26:58.700
I didn't even tell Hyeong-wook,

26:59.200 --> 27:01.328
Na-ri, or Ha-joon.

27:02.746 --> 27:04.164
She just kinda knew it.

27:08.960 --> 27:10.587
What do I do now?

27:12.005 --> 27:14.132
I'm already on her shit list.

27:15.550 --> 27:17.886
Oh, I'm too young to die.

27:24.976 --> 27:27.395
AUNT JI-SUN,
I MADE THE NATIONAL RESERVE TEAM!

27:31.483 --> 27:32.359
Oh?

27:33.610 --> 27:34.778
MISSED CALLS
HYEONG-WOOK (39)

27:34.861 --> 27:36.154
Is there something wrong?

27:39.574 --> 27:42.661
CONGRATULATIONS. ON DUTY, SO I WON'T
BE HOME. ORDER SOMETHING WITH MY CARD.

27:42.744 --> 27:43.703
Alone again.

27:56.132 --> 27:58.593
UP FOR CHICKEN?

28:01.262 --> 28:02.389
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

28:02.472 --> 28:04.391
This is so good.
I'm gonna eat the whole thing.

28:05.642 --> 28:07.227
Thanks to you, I eat well.

28:08.436 --> 28:09.646
Thanks to my aunt.

28:09.729 --> 28:12.649
I'll definitely thank her in person
when I see her. Seriously.

28:12.732 --> 28:13.566
Hm. Great.

28:14.526 --> 28:16.861
-Mind if I brag about it to the others?
-Go ahead.

28:18.947 --> 28:19.989
Oh my God.

28:21.157 --> 28:23.952
I didn't tell you. I missed
a bunch of calls from Hyeong-wook today.

28:24.035 --> 28:25.704
From Hyeong-wook? Why?

28:25.787 --> 28:26.913
I don't know.

28:27.831 --> 28:29.374
-I'll call him back.
-Okay.

28:42.679 --> 28:44.097
STOP SULKING AND COME DRINK!

28:45.640 --> 28:51.146
HEY, I'M UNDERAGE. I CAN'T EVEN GET IN

28:52.981 --> 28:54.524
SEND ME YOUR ID PHOTO ON TELEGRAM

29:01.573 --> 29:02.866
Yeah, don't test me 

29:03.575 --> 29:04.576
Can't bust me

29:05.076 --> 29:06.077
Queen of the scene

29:06.995 --> 29:08.580
Yo, come watch me

29:09.080 --> 29:10.248
Don't test me

29:10.790 --> 29:11.666
Can't bust me

29:14.335 --> 29:15.628
I made it!

29:16.212 --> 29:18.214
Hey, what took you so long?

29:19.215 --> 29:21.050
This wizardry is next level.

29:21.134 --> 29:24.304
I'm shocked it fooled the QR scanner.
You should sell these and make money.

29:24.387 --> 29:26.598
Nah. Unfortunately, that's not my work,
just so you know.

29:26.681 --> 29:27.807
If it's not yours, who then?

29:28.975 --> 29:29.851
No fucking way!

29:31.728 --> 29:32.812
Hee-jin!

29:42.489 --> 29:43.490
THE REPAIR IS DONE

29:43.573 --> 29:46.701
I'LL SEND YOU THE TRACKING NUMBER
ONCE IT SHIPS TOMORROW

30:06.012 --> 30:07.388
HYEONG-WOOK

30:08.097 --> 30:08.932
It's Girigo.

30:09.015 --> 30:11.851
And the other perfect score
is… Hyeong-wook.

30:12.435 --> 30:13.353
There's no way.

30:16.981 --> 30:17.982
KANG HA-YOUNG

30:20.735 --> 30:22.445
Why is she calling all of a sudden?

30:34.249 --> 30:36.960
Hey, Hyeong-wook. I saw
you called me a bunch. What's going on?

30:37.585 --> 30:39.504
You're the one who called me first.

30:39.587 --> 30:40.421
I did?

30:41.840 --> 30:44.717
Wha… Can you speak up?
I can't hear a word you're saying.

30:46.052 --> 30:47.053
You

30:48.221 --> 30:49.764
said you weren't coming to my birthday.

30:51.391 --> 30:54.561
Oh, I'm so sorry. I can't come.

30:54.644 --> 30:57.021
I found out
I have to train on the weekends now.

31:00.024 --> 31:01.276
What the… He hung up.

31:03.152 --> 31:05.530
The person
you are trying to reach is unavailable.

31:08.867 --> 31:10.034
He sounds upset.

31:11.661 --> 31:12.537
Weird.

31:12.620 --> 31:14.455
How did he even know that?

31:14.998 --> 31:18.084
Yeah, right. I only just found out myself.

31:21.504 --> 31:25.425
I'm just, I don't know,
maybe a little self-absorbed lately.

31:27.176 --> 31:29.596
I forgive you
since you just received bad news.

31:29.679 --> 31:31.764
Wasting weekends on training.

31:32.432 --> 31:34.392
And so, are you going to the party?

31:34.475 --> 31:37.061
Of course I'm going to the party.
He's my best friend.

31:38.396 --> 31:40.940
That's nice. You're very kind.

31:43.359 --> 31:45.904
Are you worried about Na-ri being there?

31:45.987 --> 31:47.655
How dare you?

31:47.739 --> 31:48.698
Absolutely not!

31:48.781 --> 31:51.200
It's cute. You're mad.

31:52.535 --> 31:54.787
Should I ask the coach
to push the training to next week?

31:57.373 --> 31:58.708
Hm.

32:00.877 --> 32:02.045
What are you doing?

32:02.587 --> 32:03.713
Geon-woo?

32:03.796 --> 32:06.799
October 24, 2008.

32:07.300 --> 32:08.468
Name.

32:11.054 --> 32:12.013
There we go.

32:17.727 --> 32:19.354
OCTOBER 24, 2008
KIM GEON-WOO

32:19.437 --> 32:22.690
Okay. Please let Se-ah's training
be canceled this weekend.

32:22.774 --> 32:24.275
Stop. I don't want…

32:24.901 --> 32:28.321
If it granted a perfect score in math,
why shouldn't it cancel training? Huh.

32:28.404 --> 32:31.074
-What are you doing?
-Training is canceled!

32:31.157 --> 32:33.701
Training is canceled.
Training is canceled!

32:33.785 --> 32:35.662
Training is canceled!

32:35.745 --> 32:38.748
-Training is canceled!
-Please grant my Geon-woo's wish.

32:38.831 --> 32:41.918
-Training canceled. Canceled.
-It's not real, dummy.

32:42.001 --> 32:44.295
-Training canceled.
-Just sit down and finish your chicken.

32:44.379 --> 32:46.547
-We should send this.
-You're such a goof!

32:46.631 --> 32:48.508
SENDING WISH…

32:49.592 --> 32:51.386
Here. Take this one.

32:52.220 --> 32:53.429
-You full?
-Mm-hmm.

32:54.389 --> 32:55.348
One more.

33:06.150 --> 33:07.860
FRIDAY, JUNE 13

33:15.994 --> 33:17.578
SLEEPING IN AGAIN?

33:18.746 --> 33:19.580
JUST 5 MINUTES!

33:25.169 --> 33:26.504
Whoo!

33:42.478 --> 33:44.188
Doors closing.

33:47.191 --> 33:48.192
One more time?

33:48.276 --> 33:49.610
-Not today!
-Agh!

34:00.788 --> 34:03.541
-Did the others already go in?
-I don't know.

34:03.624 --> 34:05.376
Yeah. Over here.

34:10.465 --> 34:12.592
Come on. You don't have any proof.

34:12.675 --> 34:15.386
All right, rise and shine.
Let's get started.

34:15.470 --> 34:18.097
Good morning, teacher.

34:18.181 --> 34:20.099
Let's see who's absent. Uh…

34:20.683 --> 34:22.560
Where's Na-ri? Not here yet?

34:22.643 --> 34:24.604
I don't know, sir. I haven't seen her.

34:25.104 --> 34:28.316
Well, she probably slept in again. Okay.

34:29.567 --> 34:33.529
Uh, did anyone
see or talk to Na-ri last night?

34:34.030 --> 34:36.032
-No, not me.
-Uh, no.

34:36.532 --> 34:38.618
-She's not my friend.
-No one?

34:38.701 --> 34:40.995
Tell her to visit the principal's office
when she gets here.

34:45.208 --> 34:47.126
I heard a phone. Who was that?

34:49.420 --> 34:50.713
Hyeong-wook?

34:50.797 --> 34:51.923
Are you sleeping?

34:52.006 --> 34:53.174
Yo. Hey!

34:53.841 --> 34:56.385
Buddy, he's getting mad. Get up now. Hey.

34:56.886 --> 34:58.554
Hyeong-wook?

34:58.638 --> 35:00.223
Stop fooling around. Get up.

35:01.641 --> 35:04.310
Buddy. Hey. Get up already.

35:05.853 --> 35:06.938
Hyeong-wook!

35:10.149 --> 35:11.859
Hey, calm down!

35:12.568 --> 35:15.113
-What's wrong with you?
-Give him space! Talk to me!

35:15.196 --> 35:16.322
He's in shock! Please, sir!

35:16.405 --> 35:17.865
You! Go get the school nurse.

35:17.949 --> 35:21.160
Hey, wake up. Wake up.
Wake up now! Hyeong-wook! Wake up!

35:30.002 --> 35:32.505
-Are you okay?
-Stay still.

35:33.089 --> 35:34.090
Take it easy.

35:35.216 --> 35:36.843
-What happened?
-Are you okay?

35:36.926 --> 35:38.302
-Take it slow.
-You should sit down.

35:47.353 --> 35:48.563
Hey.

35:48.646 --> 35:51.232
Hey, hey! Hyeong-wook! Put that down. Now.

35:52.024 --> 35:53.067
What are you doing?

35:53.151 --> 35:55.027
-Come on, man.
-You'll hurt yourself.

35:55.111 --> 35:56.362
Give it!

35:58.364 --> 36:00.575
Oh, watch out!

36:00.658 --> 36:02.076
Geon-woo! You okay?

36:04.328 --> 36:07.081
Careful, everyone! Stop this right now!

36:07.165 --> 36:09.000
Hyeong-wook?

36:13.337 --> 36:16.591
Just put it down. Drop it!
What are you doing to yourself?

36:17.842 --> 36:19.260
We should talk about this.

36:22.805 --> 36:25.766
Get away! Get out of here!

36:25.850 --> 36:27.977
Or you'll be fucking sorry!

36:30.646 --> 36:33.232
Hyeong-wook… we're friends.

36:33.941 --> 36:35.026
Die!

36:49.582 --> 36:50.750
I'm a loser.

36:51.334 --> 36:52.627
No, you're not.

36:58.049 --> 36:59.759
Listen. Put it away.

37:01.886 --> 37:03.763
You have to fight it. Just let it go.

37:05.598 --> 37:06.807
-No!
-Stop it.

37:08.142 --> 37:11.771
What are you doing? Stop! Stop! Please!

37:11.854 --> 37:13.898
Stop!

37:28.746 --> 37:31.040
No!

37:36.087 --> 37:38.172
No! No!

37:53.980 --> 37:56.482
-Get inside! Get inside now!
-Oh, Hyeong-wook.
